b'       INDIAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY MADRAS Academic Section   &nbs;p;&nbsp;&nbs;p;&nbsp;&nbs;p; &nbsp; Circular No. 12A /JN2016/B2/2016 Dated 31.10.201  Dear Students,  &nbs;p; Sub: Teacher Course Feedback (TCF)  Procedure to be followed E2 reg.   TCF period  31 st  October 2016 to 4 th  It is the responsibility of the students to provide Teacher Course Feedback (TCF) for each of the courses that they have credited. This provides valuable feedback to course faculty as well as to the Institute. The TCF of JulNov 2016 semester will be sought online through academic section portal.  Please follow the steps mentioned below:  Access   and login using your LDAP user id and password Click on TCF form from the menu on the left hand side The courses you have credited will be populated with the name of the instructor Select each course to fill the TCF form for that course In case of courses with multiple teachers handling a course, choose the instructor(s) who is/are handling the course.  TCF portal will be open from 31.10.2016 to 04.11.2016.  Please make sure that you complete the process within this duration.   Deputy Registrar (Courses)  To All Students through students@list.iitm.ac.in '

